Intro

Temple of Clear Skies

Infobox

Details

Population: large
Primary Species: Drows
Climate: Cool
Ruled By: Syrune

Residents

Syrune
Tyria
Gnosis(formerly)

 The Temple of Clear Skies lies far within the clouds of a mountainous region. It takes several hours to reach the temple. Many travelers become ill from the altitude change; others die from the mountainous creatures that lurk in caves following the trails. Due to the location and strict rules, many members dont venture outside the temple walls. The temple mainly survives off trading their luxurious and sometimes magical gemstones, mined from the caves.

The Temple worships a cloud giant named Plumaria. She is the giant which is believed to maintain the clear skies over the temple. These skies have allowed many members to freely study the stars and hone their rune magic. Plumaria was a great fighter who used runes to control the clouds to her bidding. In most depictions, she wears an opulent robe decorated with runes and illustrations documenting her victories over other giants.

The temple runs in a village fashion. Newborns are raised in a community rather than by individual parents. All members are taught combat but typically women specialize in archery, men in melee combat
(with scimitars), and either can learn rune magic if they want.

Members of the temple are placed in one of 3 levels/rankings:

  • Workers of Plumaria
  • Speaker of Plumaria
  • Hand of Plumaria

Workers of Plumaria are the lowest rank of members. Members within this rank are mainly young/teen members who follow strict routines of worship and schooling. To graduate to the next rank, members must pass a combat test.

Speaker(s) of Plumaria is the most common rank and participates in many different jobs around the temple. Some are traders, bakers, historians, educators, etc. To graduate to the next rank, members must pass a combat test, an endurance test, and a rune magic test. Additionally, they go through a strict selection process by the Head of the Temple.

Hand(s) of Plumaria are the highest rank any regular member can be. These members are usually guards/fighters who venture out of the temple. These members are allowed in sacred sites and are right-hand mans to the temple head. When selecting a new temple head, members of this rank are considered.
